    "extras": [
      "May to September is the sweet spot for Estonia because ferry timetables, beach weather, bog boardwalks, and long daylight all line up best in these months.",
      "Tallinn and Tartu are the easiest pair by Elron train, while Lux Express is the most comfortable way to connect Tartu, Pärnu, and longer bus legs with assigned seats and onboard Wi-Fi.",
      "If you only have a week, keep Tallinn, Lahemaa, Tartu, and either Pärnu or Saaremaa; Haapsalu is the first place to cut because it is more about mood than must-see sights.",
      "Kuressaare is the best Saaremaa base because you get the island's strongest hotel choice, walkable dining, and the castle without needing to drive after dinner.",
      "Book island stays and car rentals early for July and midsummer because Saaremaa and Pärnu fill much faster than Tallinn or Tartu.",
      "Most paid sights in Estonia are moderate by Nordic standards, so the main budget swing comes from hotel rates in Tallinn summer weekends and on Saaremaa in peak season."
    ],
